title: >>> The EXPECTATIONS
body_text:
The undefeated Joe Kelly goes one-on-one in perhaps his most crucial encounter yet against young star Lenny Herrera. This will certainly be a war for the ages; either the greatest run in dodgeball history comes crashing down or the incredible journey continues right through DODGEBALL 43.
___________________
With DODGEBALL 41's astounding numbers, it is often wondered what the numbers will say this week.
Remember, three of the biggest records were broken last week:
I. Female participation set a new record with 13, beating out DODGEBALL 20 with 11.
II. The most new blood with 15, beating the previous record of 11 at both DODGEBALL DAY 2 and DODGEBALL XXV.
III. A brand new overall attendance record of 47, finally beating DODGEBALL XTWO which had 42.
And to add to the stats, ever since DODGEBALL 36 on April 22nd, attendance has not seen a decrease.
DODGEBALL 36: 12 players
DODGEBALL XXX-SEVEN: 27 players
DODGEBALL 38: 29 players
DODGEBALL 39: 29 players
DODGEBALL XL: 36 players
DODGEBALL 41: 47 players
Make your prediction! What do you think will happen at DODGEBALL 42!?
